name: Asean and the New Order - The Volatilian‚Ñ¢
message:
Now that some of the dust has settled as the historic Association of Southeast Asian Nations (Asean) year ‚Äì its 50th ‚Äì draws to a close with its finale summit in Clark, Pampanga and its gala celebrations in Manila, the world is starting to see a new order emerging. And Philippine President Rodrigo Duterte has played no small part in that. In fact, in some ways, you could say he‚Äôs a key architect.

This will send shudders through the Left Liberal establishments from Washington to Ottawa to Brussels to Sydney and to Manila where a rump of the Liberal Party has been undermining Duterte since he took over the presidency from them 17 months ago.
